Find And Author Extensions To The Ready4 Framework

Source: vignettes/V_04.Rmd
V_04.Rmd
library("ready4")

Motivation

The ready4 package provides a “bare-bones” framework that is designed to be extended by other work. This vignette briefly summarises some examples of current extensions to the framework.

Code libraries

A standardised workflow for authoring code libraries (R packages) that extend the ready4 framework is supported by the ready4pack package. A table of the most up to date list of R package extensions to the ready4 framework can be generated using the make_pkg_extensions_tb function.

x <- make_pkg_extensions_tb()

A HTML version of the table can be printed using print_pkg_extensions.

print_pkg_extensions(x)
Type Logo Package Authors DOI
ready4class: Create, Extend and Document Ready4 Framework Classes and Methods Matthew Hamilton, Glen Wiesner
ready4fun: Author and Document R Package Functions that Extend the Ready4 Matthew Hamilton, Glen Wiesner
ready4pack: Author R Packages that Extend the Ready4 Framework Matthew Hamilton
ready4show: Author Literate Programs to Share Insights from Applying the Ready4 Matthew Hamilton, Glen Wiesner
ready4use: Author, Retrieve and Share Ready4 Framework Datasets Matthew Hamilton, Glen Wiesner
youthvars: Describe Variables Used to Characterize Youth Populations Matthew Hamilton, Caroline Gao
scorz: Derive Summary Scores from Questionnaire Item Responses Matthew Hamilton, Caroline Gao
